==English==
{{was wotd|2008|June|14}}
===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|ȝameren}}, {{m|enm|ȝaumeren}}, {{m|enm|yemeren}}, {{m|enm|ȝomeren}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġeōmrian|t=to lament}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*jāmarōn}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*jēmarōną|t=to show misery or sadness}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*jēmaraz|t=miserable, sorrowful, sad}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*yem-|t=to hold, match, defeat}}. Reinforced by cognate {{der|en|dum|jammeren}} (modern {{cog|nl|jammeren}}), from the same ultimate origin. Cognate also with {{cog|sco|yammer}}, {{cog|stq|jammerje}}, {{cog|fy|jammerje}}, {{cog|nds-de|jammern}}, {{cog|de|jammern}}, {{cog|da|jamre}}, {{cog|no|jamre}}. Compare also {{cog|non|amra|t=to howl, wail, yammer}}.
===Pronunciation===
